      <h1>Who We Are</h1>
      <p>The Break the Cycle YCAP project sought to curb cyber addiction among Grade 9 learners, fostering healthier technology habits. Although developed without sponsorships or direct data, its potential impact is drawn from its interventions, targeting the widespread academic and social challenges linked to excessive digital use.</p>
      
    </section>
    
    <section class="Mission">
      <h1>Our Mission</h1>
      <p>The project aims to reduce cyber addiction and its negative effects on Grade 9 students.</p>
      <p>It promotes academic integrity by addressing plagiarism and underperformance.</p>
      <p>It seeks to foster healthier digital habits and overall student well-being.</p>
    </section>
    
    <section class="vision">
      <h1>Our Vision</h1>
      
      <p>The "Break the Cycle" project envisions helping Grade 9 learners develop a healthier relationship with technology while improving academic integrity and overall well-being</p>
      <p>It aims to create a supportive school environment where students are engaged, responsible online, and equipped to manage cyber addiction.</p>
